The first is a new contravision site on Pybus, a stone’s throw from Guerrilla’s site at 92 Rivonia Road. This time the landlord partner is Redefine and the first client on board is AB InBev for brand Stella Artois.<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1810/466159-625x833.jpg" alt="Enriching the richest square mile in Africa" width="625" height="833">The second newsworthy development was a bespoke, eye catching execution for client Cadbury. The campaign’s creative concept was ‘Re-gifting Anything’ – including in this case a billboard. The Guerrillas worked tirelessly to make this mega board on Grayston look like it had been re-wrapped and re-gifted, bring the concept to life on an XXXL scale!<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1810/466162.jpg" alt="Enriching the richest square mile in Africa" width="309" height="552" rel="">click to enlarge<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1810/466164.jpg" alt="Enriching the richest square mile in Africa" width="309" height="552" rel="">click to enlarge<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1810/466166.jpg" alt="Enriching the richest square mile in Africa" width="309" height="552" rel="">click to enlargeThese are just two of many exciting developments as Guerrilla IMC chases big growth as it celebrates it’s 10th birthday.